[{"id":43817,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given $P_1 = 8$ bar $= 8 \\times 10^5$ Pa, $V_1 = 0.15$ m$^3$, and $P_2 = 1$ bar $= 10^5$ Pa.<br><br>The adiabatic index $\\gamma$ is given by:<br><br>$\\gamma = \\dfrac{c_p}{c_v} = \\dfrac{3R}{2R} = 1.5$<br><br>For an adiabatic process, $P_1 V_1^\\gamma = P_2 V_2^\\gamma$.<br><br>$V_2 = V_1 \\left( \\dfrac{P_1}{P_2} \\right)^{\\dfrac{1}{\\gamma}}$<br><br>$V_2 = 0.15 \\times \\left( \\dfrac{8}{1} \\right)^{\\dfrac{1}{1.5}} = 0.15 \\times 8^{\\dfrac{2}{3}} = 0.15 \\times 4 = 0.6$ m$^3$<br><br>The work done during the adiabatic expansion is:<br><br>$W = \\dfrac{P_1 V_1 - P_2 V_2}{\\gamma - 1}$<br><br>$W = \\dfrac{8 \\times 10^5 \\times 0.15 - 1 \\times 10^5 \\times 0.6}{1.5 - 1}$<br><br>$W = \\dfrac{1.2 \\times 10^5 - 0.6 \\times 10^5}{0.5}$<br><br>$W = \\dfrac{0.6 \\times 10^5}{0.5} = 1.2 \\times 10^5$ J<br><br>$W = 120$ kJ<br><br>Answer: $120$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":43883,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>525</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>441</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>572</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>735</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>For isobaric process and diatomic gas we can write,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>735</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>n</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>7</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>735</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>210</mn></math></p><p>Now internal energy will be,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>V</mi></msub><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi>R</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"/><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>210</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>525</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43931,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Process of isothermal</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mfrac><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>17258</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43962,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<math><mi>P</mi><msup><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math><br /><math><mi>T</mi><msup><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math><br /><math><mn>300</mn><mi></mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1.4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mi></mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br />Now for BC process<br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi></mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi></mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1818.859</mn></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1819</mn><mi></mi><mi>K</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fefec39d-c84f-42af-b368-089e652d4f11.jpeg\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43845,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$5 \\pi$","$40 \\pi$","$10 \\pi$","zero"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6S9FiJB_lQtZHWjLhiFsPat-2oggwDXTMvoh5o9pGDQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>\n\n\n\n$\\begin{aligned} & \\mathrm{W}=\\frac{1}{2} \\pi \\mathrm{R}^2 \\\\ & =\\frac{1}{2} \\times \\pi \\times\\left(\\frac{200}{2} \\times 10^3\\right) \\times \\frac{200}{2} \\times 10^{-6} \\\\ & =\\frac{10 \\pi}{2}=5 \\pi \\mathrm{~J}\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (24 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43997,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a1963d6d-1d3f-4c22-9fb1-419878818f13-image.png\" style=\"width: 186px; height: 187px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/652e2071-53ac-4af2-a942-e391a4d9a005-image.png\" style=\"width: 182px; height: 186px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4620bc1c-09cd-4f56-87b1-d8d1b666fb8f-image.png\" style=\"width: 177px; height: 183px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/55331c29-a7c7-4aea-b98a-7416b4e55e10-image.png\" style=\"width: 184px; height: 189px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"Is an adiabatic process<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><msup><mi>V</mi><mrow><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>t</mi><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>V</mi><msup><mi>T</mi><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></msup><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>t</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> as T increase V decreases at non-uniform rate<br /><br />In process <math><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>b</mi></math> P = constant as <math><mi>V</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>T</mi></math><br /><br />In process <math><mi>c</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>d</mi></math> <math><msup><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>&#8242;</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo></math> constant s <math><mi>V</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>T</mi></math><br /><br />But since slope of V - T graph <math><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />since slope of ab &lt; slope of cd<br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>b</mi></mrow></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mrow><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>d</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br />Also in adiabatic process <math><mi>d</mi><mo>&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></math> as T is increasing V in decreasing<br /><br /><math><mo>&#8658;</mo></math> P is increasing, so P - V diagram is as below<br /><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a1963d6d-1d3f-4c22-9fb1-419878818f13-image.png\" style=\"width: 186px; height: 187px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":44028,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$6 \\mathrm{~cal}$","$16 \\mathrm{~cal}$.","$66 \\mathrm{~cal}$.","$14 \\mathrm{~cal}$."],"answer":0,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2007","image":null},{"id":44008,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$1.5$","$1.4$","$1.3$","$1.6$"],"answer":1,"solution":"Volume of the gas $\\mathrm{v}=\\frac{\\mathrm{m}}{\\mathrm{d}}$ and using $\\mathrm{PV}^\\gamma=$ constant\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{\\mathrm{P}^{\\prime}}{\\mathrm{P}}=\\frac{\\mathrm{V}}{\\mathrm{V}^{\\prime}}=\\left(\\frac{\\mathrm{d}^{\\prime}}{\\mathrm{d}}\\right)^\\gamma \\\\\n& \\text { or } 128=(32)^\\gamma \\\\\n& \\therefore \\gamma=\\frac{7}{5}=1.4\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2013 (22 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":43843,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"$\\begin{aligned} V & =\\text { constant } \\\\ \\frac{P_1}{T_1} & =\\frac{P_2}{T_2} \\\\ P_2 & =2 P_1 \\\\ T_2 & =2 T_1 \\\\ & =2 \\times 300=600 \\mathrm{~K} \\\\ \\therefore T_2 & =327^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\\end{aligned}","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":43809,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$3$","$4$","$14$","$9$"],"answer":1,"solution":"The right compartment is enclosed by adiabatic walls and an adiabatic piston, and no heat is supplied to it. Therefore, the gas in the right compartment undergoes an adiabatic compression.<br><br>Since the piston is frictionless, the pressure in the right compartment is always equal to the pressure in the left compartment. The final pressure in both compartments is $P_f = \\dfrac{27P}{8}$.<br><br>For the adiabatic process in the right compartment, the equation is:<br>$P_i V_i^\\gamma = P_f V_f^\\gamma$<br><br>Given $P_i = P$, $V_i = 9$ L, $P_f = \\dfrac{27P}{8}$, and $\\gamma = \\dfrac{C_P}{C_V} = 1.5 = \\dfrac{3}{2}$. Substituting these values:<br>$P(9)^{3/2} = \\left(\\dfrac{27P}{8}\\right) V_f^{3/2}$<br><br>Since $9^{3/2} = (3^2)^{3/2} = 3^3 = 27$, the equation becomes:<br>$27P = \\dfrac{27P}{8} V_f^{3/2}$<br><br>Dividing both sides by $27P$:<br>$1 = \\dfrac{1}{8} V_f^{3/2}$<br><br>$V_f^{3/2} = 8$<br><br>Taking the power of $2/3$ on both sides:<br>$V_f = (8)^{2/3} = (2^3)^{2/3} = 2^2 = 4$ litres.<br><br>Answer: $4$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (06 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43930,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0c365369-92dc-4459-a1f6-0d74e162082d-image.png\" style=\"width: 169px; height: 172px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/35f7586c-634d-43fa-9a94-adfda2b048d0-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 171px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/28132133-3e72-469a-876e-6f7de76c8b28-image.png\" style=\"width: 155px; height: 162px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/36c99d2c-8a85-469c-995c-562fc8d876c6-image.png\" style=\"width: 166px; height: 170px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mi>T</mi></math></p><p>Straight line with positive slope <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43911,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>","Insufficient data to draw any conclusion"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>We know that the ideal gas equation of gas is</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi></math></p><p>Keeping the temperature constant, we have,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>&#8733;</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>P</mi></mfrac></math></p><p>As seen from graph,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>, so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#62;</mo><msub><mi>P</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (27 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44018,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$327^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$200^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$54^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$","$300^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given, $V_1=V$\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& V_2=2 V \\\\\n& T_1=27^{\\circ}+273=300 \\mathrm{~K} \\\\\n& T_2=?\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nFrom charle's law\n$$\n\\frac{V_1}{T_1}=\\frac{V_2}{T_2}(\\because \\text { Pressure is constant })\n$$\nor, $\\frac{V}{300}=\\frac{2 V}{T_2}$\n\n$$\n\\therefore \\quad T_2=600 \\mathrm{~K}=600-273=327^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (07 May Online)","image":null},{"id":43914,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/928c1b20-13f8-44d1-97f7-f42cc7e6fdad-image.png\" style=\"width: 280px; height: 136px;\" /></p><p>Using the relation,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math></p><p>Or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>180</mn><mn>300</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>324</mn><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>324</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn></mrow><mn>180</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>540</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (26 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43982,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math><mn>500</mn><mi> </mi><mi>K</mi></math>","<math><mn>400</mn><mi> </mi><mi>K</mi></math>","<math><mn>300</mn><mi> </mi><mi>K</mi></math>","<math><mn>600</mn><mi> </mi><mi>K</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hmkxvkpqqomsbpzjbhjzpdyaftbycwctyabcdqbsjbggszdmjl.png\" /> <br/><br/> <math><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math> <br/><br/> <math><mo>⇒</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> <br/><br/> <math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math> <br/><br/> <math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>500</mn><mi>K</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":44000,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>8</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>4</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mn>2</mn><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Change in entropy,&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtable columnalign=\"left\"><mtr><mtd><mi>d</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>heat</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>supplied</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>}</mo></mrow></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>d</mi><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>t</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>d</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext>Intergrating</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>both</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>sides</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><munderover><mo>&#8747;</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>f</mi></msub></munderover><mi>d</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>&#8747;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>d</mi><mi>T</mi></mrow><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>f</mi></msub><mo>&#8722;</mo><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>.</mo><mi>ln</mi><mi>T</mi><msubsup><mo>|</mo><mn>100</mn><mn>200</mn></msubsup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mrow><mo>[</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>200</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>100</mn><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext>and</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>&#8658;</mo><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mtext>&#8201;</mtext><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>S</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext>Entrpoy&#160;change&#160;in&#160;same&#160;for&#160;both&#160;cases&#160;as&#160;C&#160;is&#160;constant,&#160;and</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mtext>temperature&#160;change&#160;(i</mtext><mtext>.e</mtext><mtext>.&#160;from&#160;100&#160;to&#160;200)&#160;is&#160;same</mtext><mtext>.</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":44022,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$372 \\mathrm{~K}$ and $330 \\mathrm{~K}$","$330 \\mathrm{~K}$ and $268 \\mathrm{~K}$","$310 \\mathrm{~K}$ and $248 \\mathrm{~K}$","$372 \\mathrm{~K}$ and $310 \\mathrm{~K}$"],"answer":3,"solution":"$\\eta_1=\\frac{T_1-T_2}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{6}$\n$\\eta_2=\\frac{T_1-\\left(T_2-62\\right)}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{3}$\n$\\Rightarrow \\frac{T_1-T_2}{T_1}+\\frac{62}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{3}$\n$\\frac{1}{6}+\\frac{62}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{3}$\n$\\frac{62}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{6}$\n$\\therefore T_1=62 \\times 6=372 \\mathrm{~K}$\n$\\frac{T_1-T_2}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{6}$\n$1-\\frac{T_2}{T_1}=\\frac{1}{6}$\n$\\frac{T_2}{372}=\\frac{5}{6}$\n$\\Rightarrow T_2=310 \\mathrm{~K}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2011","image":null},{"id":43906,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>As we know, in isobaric process pressure remains constant and magnitude of slope of adiabatic curve will be more than the isothermal curve at the common point, therefore diagram for process will be as given below.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/867db2a6-a4da-4624-aeaa-b5fad7e5a5ff-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 161px;\" /></p><p>Also,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo></math> area under&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>V</mi></math>&nbsp;curve.</p><p>Hence,</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&#60;</mo><msub><mi>W</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jun Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43983,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&nbsp;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math><mn>80</mn><mi> </mi><mi>J</mi></math>"],"answer":2,"solution":"For path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ACB</mi></math>,<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#916;U</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#916;W</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>&#916;U</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>30</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>&#916;U</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math><br /><br />For path <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ADB</mi></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>&#916;U</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>&#916;W</mi></math><br /><br />As initial and find points are the same, change in internal energy is same in both the cases<br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>&#916;Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn><mi>&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":44021,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["efficiency of Carnot engine cannot be made larger than $50 \\%$","$1200 \\mathrm{~K}$","$750 \\mathrm{~K}$","$600 \\mathrm{~K}$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$\\frac{40}{100}=\\frac{500-T_S}{500}, T_S=300 \\mathrm{~K}$\n$\\frac{600}{100}=\\frac{T-300}{T} \\Rightarrow T=750 \\mathrm{~K}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (Offline)","image":null},{"id":43823,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["-30","-189","-117","-56"],"answer":3,"solution":"For isothermal expansion of 1 mole diatomic gas from V to 2V at 300 K:<br>$W = RT\\ln 2 = R(300)\\ln 2$ <br>For adiabatic expansion with same volume change and same work output:<br>$W = nC_V\\Delta T = C_V(T_i - T_f)$ <br>For diatomic gas, $C_V = \\frac{5}{2}R$. Setting work equal:<br>$R(300)\\ln 2 = \\frac{5}{2}R(300 - T_f)$ <br>Simplifying:<br>$300\\ln 2 = 2.5(300 - T_f)$, so $300(0.693) = 2.5(300 - T_f)$ <br>$207.9 = 750 - 2.5T_f$, giving $T_f = 216.84$ K $\\approx$ -56°C.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43989,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>772</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>420</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2100</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2520</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<math> <mrow> <mi>&#951;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#8722;</mo><mfrac> <mrow> <msub> <mi>T</mi> <mn>2</mn> </msub> </mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mi>T</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </mrow> </mfrac> </mrow> </math>, efficiency <math><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>W</mi></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>W</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>250</mn><mn>300</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>W</mi><mrow><msub><mi>Q</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>+</mo><mi>W</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>420</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":44016,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["$2 \\sqrt{2} T$","$4 T$","$2 T$","$8 T$"],"answer":2,"solution":"$T V^{\\gamma-1}=$ constant\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& T_1 V_1^{\\gamma-1}=\\mathrm{T}_2 V_2^{\\gamma-1} \\\\\n& \\Rightarrow T(V)^{1 / 2}=\\mathrm{T}_2\\left(\\frac{V}{4}\\right)^{1 / 2} \\\\\n& {\\left[\\because \\gamma=1.5, T_1=T, V_1=V \\text { and } V_2=\\frac{V}{4}\\right]} \\\\\n& \\therefore \\quad T_2=\\left(\\frac{4 V}{V}\\right)^{1 / 2} T=2 T\n\\end{aligned}\n$$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (12 May Online)","image":null},{"id":43831,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["(A)-(IV), (B)-(III), (C)-(II), (D)-(I)","(A)-(IV), (B)-(I), (C)-(III), (D)-(II)","(A)-(IV), (B)-(II), (C)-(III), (D)-(I)","(A)-(II), (B)-(IV), (C)-(III), (D)-(I)"],"answer":2,"solution":"(A) Isobaric $(\\mathrm{P}=\\mathrm{C})$<br/>$\\Delta \\mathrm{Q}=\\Delta \\mathrm{U}+\\mathrm{P} \\Delta \\mathrm{~V}$<br/>(B) Isochoric $(\\mathrm{V}=\\mathrm{C})$<br/>$\\Delta \\mathrm{Q}=\\Delta \\mathrm{U}$<br/>(C) Adiabatic $(\\Delta \\mathrm{Q}=0)$<br/>$\\Delta \\mathrm{Q}=0$<br/>(D) Isothermal $(\\Delta \\mathrm{U}=0)$<br/>$\\Delta \\mathrm{Q}=\\Delta \\mathrm{W}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43848,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"Given that process is isobaric $\\Delta \\mathrm{T}=50^{\\circ} \\mathrm{C}$\nQ in isobaric process $=\\mathrm{nC}_{\\mathrm{p}} \\Delta \\mathrm{T}=\\mathrm{E}_1$\n$\\Delta \\mathrm{U}$ in isobaric process $=\\mathrm{nC}_{\\mathrm{v}} \\Delta \\mathrm{T}=\\mathrm{E}_2$\n$\\therefore \\frac{\\mathrm{E}_1}{\\mathrm{E}_2}=\\frac{\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{P}}}{\\mathrm{C}_{\\mathrm{v}}}=\\gamma$\n\nGiven, gas is monoatomic\n$\\begin{aligned}\n\\therefore \\gamma & =1+\\frac{2}{\\mathrm{f}} \\\\\n& =1+\\frac{2}{3} \\\\\n& =\\frac{5}{3}\n\\end{aligned}$\n\nNow, as per question.\n$\\begin{aligned}\n& \\frac{5}{3}=\\frac{x}{9} \\\\\n& x=15\n\\end{aligned}$","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":43885,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#160;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","Zero","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Given here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p><p>From first law of thermodynamics,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>W</mi></math>, where,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi></math>&nbsp;is change in internal energy and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi></math>&nbsp;is work done.</p><p>We have,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>W</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Area</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>under</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">V</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>curve</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>&#8747;</mo><mi>P</mi><mi>d</mi><mi>V</mi></math></p><p>Here, volume decreases, hence work done by system will be negative.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4500</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":43993,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.51</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.68</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>6</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.71</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>7</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.67</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<math><mo>Q=</mo><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>336</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math><mo>&#8756;</mo><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mi>Work done</mi><mi>&#160;</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>Q</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>c</mi><mi>e</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>s</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>n</mi><mi>k</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>336</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mrow><mn>10</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mn>300</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>273</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.67</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>5</mn></msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2016 (10 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":43942,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["either monoatomic or diatomic","polyatomic only","monoatomic only","diatomic only"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>U</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>n</mi><mi>f</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mrow><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></p><p>Since degree of freedom is more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp;therefore gas is polyatomic</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":43977,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The work done in a cyclic process is equal to the area of closed P-V curve cycle.</p><p>Work done,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo></math>&nbsp;Area of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>C</mi><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></math><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&#215;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p><p>In the given P-V graph, the process is clockwise. So, the work done will be positive which means that the system is doing the work.</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":43842,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Thermodynamics","question":"","options":["change in its temperature","change in its volume","change in its pressure","change in its specific heat"],"answer":0,"solution":"Work done in adiabatic process $=\\frac{n R \\Delta T}{1-\\gamma}$\nSo, depends upon change in temperature.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (29 Jan Shift 1)","image":null}]